# Load MixSIAR package
library(MixSIAR)

library(readxl)
library(resample)
library(R2jags)
library(tidyverse)
library(dplyr)
library(sp)
library(splancs)
# load files
mydata <- read.csv("SIA/Samples.csv", sep=";", header = T,
        na.strings = "NA",
        dec = ".")

1 Mixing Polygons

1.1 Canary Islands

atl_can <- mydata %>% 
  dplyr:: filter(Area == "Canarias") %>% 
  dplyr:: select(d13C, d15N)

write.table(atl_can, "SIA/MixPol/mixture_can.csv", append = F, sep = ";", dec = ".", row.names = F, col.names = TRUE)

# load prey source, predator mixture and DTDF
sources <- read.table("SIA/MixPol/source_can.csv",header=T,sep=";") #always put 13C(x) before 15N(y)
mixture <- read.table("SIA/MixPol/mixture_can.csv",header=T,sep=";") #some error is required for every value
TEF <-  read.table("SIA/MixPol/DTDF.csv", header=T,sep=";")
its <- 1500  #specify the number of iterations ("its")
min_C <- -22  #specifiy the dimensions and resolution for the mixing region figure
max_C <- -14    #choose values outside the 95% mixing region
min_N <- 5  
max_N <- 17
res <- 250 #resolution of the mixing region figure; reducing this improves performance

##Now RUN the simulation 
step_C <- (max_C - min_C)/(res - 1)
step_N <- (max_N - min_N)/(res - 1)   
C_g <- seq(min_C,max_C,by=step_C) #values must be in ascending order
N_g <- seq(min_N,max_N,by=step_N) #values must be in ascending order
mgrid <- function(a,b) {  #create a grid of values to test for P-I-P
  list(
    x=outer(b*0,a,FUN="+"),
    y=outer(b,a*0,FUN="+")
  )
}
m <- mgrid(C_g,N_g)
Par_values <- array(0, c(its,(nrow(sources)*4+3)))  #create files to store data
p <- array(0, c(its,(nrow(mixture))))
mix_reg <- array(0, c(res,res))
for (i in 1:its) {    #run loops to generate source isotopic signatures, for iterations = 'its'
  v <- array(0, c(nrow(sources),2))
  f <- array(0, c(nrow(TEF),2))
  for (j in 1:nrow(sources)) {
    v[j,1] <- rnorm(1, mean=sources[j,1], sd=sources[j,2])  #generate values from norm. dist. for d13C
    v[j,2] <- rnorm(1, mean=sources[j,3], sd=sources[j,4])  #generate values from norm. dist. for d15N
    f[j,1] <- rnorm(1, mean=TEF[j,1], sd=TEF[j,2])  #generate values from norm. dist. for d13C enrichment
    f[j,2] <- rnorm(1, mean=TEF[j,3], sd=TEF[j,4])  #generate values from norm. dist. for d15N enrichment
  }
  V <- v+f
  hull <- chull(V)  #create a 2D convex hull from the enriched sources
  hull_a <- append(hull,hull[1])  #closes the polygon
  P <- point.in.polygon(mixture[,1], mixture[,2], V[hull_a,1], V[hull_a,2]) #calculate P_I_P 
  P_n <- as.numeric(P)      
  p[i,] <- P_n
  poly_a <- areapl(V[hull_a,])  #calculate polygon area, for evaluating the quantity of iterations
  m$y_f <- m$y[res:1,]  #flip y grid data to resemble axes (d13C=x, d15N=y) 
  m_r <- point.in.polygon(m$x, m$y_f, V[hull_a,1], V[hull_a,2]) #calculate P-I-P for the mixing region
  m_r_s <- matrix(m_r,nrow=res,byrow=F)  #convert vector into square matrix
  m_r_s[m_r_s > 1] <- 1  #point.in.polygon can return '2' or '3'
  mix_reg <- mix_reg + m_r_s
  vals <- c(v[,1],v[,2],f[,1],f[,2],0,0,0)  #concatenate values for this iteration
  Par_values[i,] <- vals  #store values
  Par_values[i,ncol(Par_values)-2] <- poly_a
  Par_values[i,ncol(Par_values)-1] <- i
  Par_values[i,ncol(Par_values)] <- var(Par_values[1:i,ncol(Par_values)-2])
  if (i %% 10 ==0) cat(paste("iteration", i, "\n")) 
}

##FIGURE 1: variance of polygon area during simulation
Iterations <- Par_values[,ncol(Par_values)-1]
Variance <- Par_values[,ncol(Par_values)]
plot(Iterations, Variance, type="n")  #plots 
lines(Iterations, Variance, lty=1, lwd=1.5, col="blue")

1.1.1 Figure S4: mixing region, consumers, average enriched source signatures

mix_reg <- mix_reg/its  #convert to 0-1 scale
mix_reg[mix_reg==0] <- NA #make the zeros white
mix_regt <- t(mix_reg[ncol(mix_reg):1,])  #transpose matrix for use with 'image'

image(C_g, N_g, mix_regt, col=colorRampPalette(c("blue", "light blue", "green", "light green", "yellow", "red"))(100), xlab="d13C", ylab="d15N", useRaster=T)
cont <- c(0.05, seq(0.1, 1, by=0.1))
contour(C_g, N_g, mix_regt, levels=cont, add=TRUE, drawlabels=T, lwd=1.9)
sources_TEF <- sources + TEF
points(sources_TEF[,1], sources_TEF[,3], col="white", pch=4, lwd=2, cex=1.5)
points(mixture, pch=19, cex=1.3)

delete points outside 95% interval

# Proportion of iterations that each consumer was inside mixing polygon
p[p > 1] <- 1   #point.in.polygon can return '2' or '3'
Probabilities <- colSums(p)/its
print(Probabilities>0.05)
##  [1]  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE
## [13]  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE FALSE
## [25]  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE
## [37]  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE FALSE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE
## [49]  TRUE FALSE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE FALSE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE
## [61]  TRUE  TRUE  TRUE FALSE  TRUE FALSE
P <- ifelse(Probabilities>0.05, 1, 0)
sum(P/nrow(atl_can)*100)
## [1] 90.90909
sum(P)
## [1] 60
mixture$insidepolygon95 <- P

atl_can <- mydata %>% 
  dplyr:: filter(Area == "Canarias" )%>% 
  dplyr:: select(d13C, d15N, Ind)

can_filtered <- merge(atl_can, mixture, by = c("d13C", "d15N")) %>% 
  dplyr:: filter(insidepolygon95 == 1) %>% 
  dplyr:: select(d13C, d15N, Ind)

write.table(can_filtered, "SIA/SWO_mix_can.csv", append = F, sep = ",", dec = ".", row.names = F, col.names = TRUE)

2 Mixing models

2.1 Canary Islands

## Load mix data
mix.filename <- "SIA/SWO_mix_can.csv"
mix <- load_mix_data(filename=mix.filename,
   iso_names=c("d13C","d15N"),
   factors= "Ind",
   fac_random=T,
   fac_nested=NULL,
   cont_effects=NULL)

## Load source data
source.filename <- "SIA/SWO_prey_sourcesCAN.csv"
source <- load_source_data(filename=source.filename,
         source_factors=NULL,
         conc_dep=FALSE,
         data_type="means",
         mix)

## Load diet-tissue discrimination factors DTDF
discr.filename <- "SIA/SWO_muscle_DTDF.csv"
discr <- load_discr_data(filename=discr.filename,
       mix)

## Define model structure and write JAGS model file
model_filename <- "SIA/OUTPUT/MixSIAR_CAN.txt"   # Name of the JAGS model file
resid_err <- F
process_err <- TRUE
write_JAGS_model(model_filename, resid_err, process_err, mix, source)

## Run the JAGS model
jags.uninf <- run_model(run="extreme",mix,source,discr,model_filename,alpha.prior = 1, resid_err, process_err)

  ## Process diagnostics, summary stats, and posterior plots
output_JAGS(jags.uninf, mix, source) 
save(jags.uninf, file = "SIA/OUTPUT/MixSIAR_CAN.RData")
